item.confluence.adhesive_bandage.info: The Adhesive Bandage is an immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Bleeding debuff. It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Rusty Armored Bones, Werewolves, and Angler Fish.
item.confluence.adhesive_bandage.info2: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Medicated Bandage, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.aglet.info: The Aglet is an accessory that increases the player's movement speed by 5%.
item.confluence.aglet.info2: It can be found in surface Chests, Wooden Crates and Pearlwood Crates.
The Amber Horseshoe Balloon is an accessory that increases jump height by 75% (6 blocks → 10.5 blocks), reduces it by 15% when underwater (8 blocks → 7 blocks), makes the player immune to fall damage, and releases bees when attacked, which seek out and damage enemies.
It can be crafted at a Tinkerer's Workshop with a Lucky Horseshoe and a Honey Balloon.
On the Desktop version Desktop version, Console version Console version, and Mobile version Mobile version, it also grants the Honey buff after being damaged.
item.confluence.amphibian_boots.info: The Amphibian Boots are an accessory crafted by combining the Sailfish Boots and Frog Leg at a Tinkerer's Workshop. It provides the benefits of both.
item.confluence.ancient_chisel.info: The Ancient Chisel is an accessory that increases mining speed by 25%, similarly to a Mining Potion. It can be found in Sandstone Chests in the Underground Desert and in Oasis Crates or Mirage Crates.
item.confluence.angler_earring.info: The Angler Earring is an accessory that increases the player's current Fishing Power by 10 when equipped.
item.confluence.angler_tackle_bag.info: The Angler Tackle Bag is an accessory that combines the functionality of its components:
item.confluence.angler_tackle_bag.info2: The Angler Earring's 10% boost to Fishing power, the Tackle Box's chance to not consume bait, and the unbreakable quality of the High Test Fishing Line.
item.confluence.angler_tackle_bag.info3: The Angler Tackle Bag's increase in fishing power stacks with that of the Angler Earring and Lavaproof Tackle Bag, granting a total boost of 30% if all three are equipped.
item.confluence.angler_tackle_bag.info4: The decreased chance to consume bait does not stack with that of the Tackle Box or the Lavaproof Tackle Bag.
item.confluence.angler_tackle_bag.toolti: Line never breaks and −5% bait consumption chance
item.confluence.ankh_charm.info: The Ankh Charm is a Hardmode immunity accessory which combines the effects of the Armor Bracing, Medicated Bandage, The Plan, Countercurse Mantra, and Reflective Shades.
item.confluence.ankh_shield.info: The Ankh Shield is a Hardmode shield and immunity accessory which provides immunity to 12, knockback immunity, and an additional 4 defense.
item.confluence.ankh_shield.info2: It is crafted from an Obsidian Shield and an Ankh Charm at the Tinkerer's Workshop.
item.confluence.anklet_of_the_wind.info: The Anklet of the Wind is an accessory that gives a 10% bonus to movement speed.
item.confluence.anklet_of_the_wind.info2: The effect also stacks with the movement speed bonus of the Aglet.
item.confluence.anklet_of_the_wind.info3: It can be found in Jungle and Bramble Crates with a 19% chance, and also in Ivy Chests located in Jungle Shrines and at the base of a Living Mahogany Tree in the Underground Jungle with a 9/40 (22.5%) chance.
item.confluence.arcane_flower.info: The Arcane Flower is a Hardmode accessory which combines the functionality of the Mana Flower and the aggro-reducing effect of the Putrid Scent.
item.confluence.arcane_flower.tooltip2: Automatically uses mana potions when needed
item.confluence.arcane_flower.tooltip3: The enemy is unlikely to target you
item.confluence.architect_gizmo_pack.too: Decreased 'Right Click Delay' by 2, cannot stack the decrease of its materials
item.confluence.argon_moss_fishing_bobbe: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.armor_bracing.info: Armor Bracing is a Hardmode immunity accessory that combines the functions of the Vitamins and the Armor Polish.
item.confluence.armor_bracing.info2: This item provides immunity from the Weak and Broken Armor debuffs.
item.confluence.armor_bracing.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Ankh Charm, which is further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.armor_bracing.tooltip: Immunity to Weakness and Broken Armor
item.confluence.armor_polish.info: The Armor Polish is a Hardmode immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Broken Armor debuff.
item.confluence.armor_polish.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 199/10000 (1.99%) chance to drop from Armored Skeletons and Blue Armored Bones.
item.confluence.armor_polish.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Armor Bracing, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.avenger_emblem.info: The Avenger Emblem is a Hardmode accessory that grants 12% increased damage to all weapons.
item.confluence.balloon_pufferfish.info: The Balloon Pufferfish is an accessory that increases the player's jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing the height that the player can jump from 6 blocks (12 feet) to ~10½ blocks (21 feet), effectively a ~75% boost;
item.confluence.balloon_pufferfish.info2: however, it oddly reduces jump height when underwater, from 8 blocks (16 feet) to 7 blocks (14 feet), meaning it grants the same jump height bonus and downside as the Shiny Red Balloon.
item.confluence.balloon_pufferfish.info3: It can be obtained via fishing in any biome.
item.confluence.band_of_regeneration.inf: The Band of Regeneration is an accessory that can be found in Gold Chests in the Underground and Cavern biomes and in Living Mahogany Trees in the Underground Jungle.
When equipped, it regenerates 1 health every second.
This effect stacks with the player's natural health regeneration, but unlike the natural regeneration, does not slow or stop when the player is moving or being attacked.
item.confluence.band_of_starpower.info: The Band of Starpower is an accessory that increases the player's maximum mana by 20.
item.confluence.band_of_starpower.info2: The Band of Starpower has a 1/5 (20%) chance of being obtained from destroying Shadow Orbs found in the Corruption or a 1/5 (20%) chance from Corrupt Crates and Defiled Crates, which are fished in the Corruption.
item.confluence.bee_cloak.info: The Bee Cloak is a Hardmode accessory that combines the effects of the Star Cloak and the Honey Comb.
item.confluence.bee_cloak.info2: When the player is injured, three stars will fall on the player's current location and bees are released.
item.confluence.berserkers_glove.info: The Berserker's Glove is a Hardmode accessory crafted from the Power Glove and Flesh Knuckles, granting the abilities of both.
item.confluence.berserkers_glove.info8: Autoswing for melee weapons and whips
item.confluence.bezoar.info: The Bezoar is an immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Poisoned debuff.
item.confluence.bezoar.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Hornets, Moss Hornets, and Toxic Sludges.
item.confluence.bezoar.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Medicated Bandage, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.black_belt.info: The Black Belt is a Hardmode, post-Plantera accessory that grants a 10% chance to dodge an attack, including instances of damage taken from hazards such as traps and lava.
item.confluence.black_belt.info2: A cloud of smoke surrounds the player upon a successful dodge.
item.confluence.black_belt.info3: The Black Belt has a 1/12 (8.33%) / 23/144 (15.97%) chance to drop from Bone Lees in the post-Plantera Dungeon.
item.confluence.blindfold.info: The Blindfold is a Hardmode immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Darkness debuff.
item.confluence.blindfold.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Corrupt Slimes, Slimelings, Crimslimes, Dark Mummies, and Blood Mummies.
item.confluence.blindfold.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Reflective Shades, which are a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.blizzard_in_a_balloon.in: The Blizzard in a Balloon is an accessory that combines the effects of the Blizzard in a Bottle and the Shiny Red Balloon.

It boosts jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing your first jump's height to ~10½ blocks (~75% increase), and provides a double jump that now goes 14½ blocks, for a total height of 25 blocks.
item.confluence.blizzard_in_a_bottle.inf: The Blizzard in a Bottle is a pre-Hardmode accessory which works similarly to the Cloud in a Bottle, allowing the player to double-jump.
Instead of a cloud being produced when the player jumps, a trail of snow is produced at the player's feet.
The Blizzard jump goes 8 tiles into the air, totaling 14 tiles when put together with the first jump.
The Blizard in a Bottle has a 1551/10000 (15.51%) chance of being found inside Frozen Chests in the Ice biome, as well as a 1/6 (16.67%) chance of being obtained from Frozen and Boreal Crates.
On the Desktop version Desktop version, Console version Console version, and Mobile version Mobile version, it can also be crafted at a Crystal Ball.
item.confluence.blue_horseshoe_balloon.i: The Blue Horseshoe Balloon is an accessory that grants immunity to fall damage, increases jump height by 75%, grants a double-jump, and grants +0.05 luck.[1] The height of the first jump is increased from 6 blocks to 10.5 blocks, while the double-jump's height is increased from 5 blocks to 9 blocks, reaching a total of 19.5 blocks with both jumps.
Jump height is instead reduced by 15% when underwater, reducing total underwater jump height from 15 blocks (8 + 7 from Cloud jump) to 13 blocks (7 + 6 from Cloud jump).
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info: The Brain of Confusion is a pre-Hardmode accessory that, upon taking damage while equipped, nearby enemies have a 3/5 (60%) chance of receiving the Confused debuff for at minimum 1.5 seconds.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info2: The chance, duration, and area of effect of the debuff are based on the amount of damage taken.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info3: Furthermore, the player wielding it has a 1/6 (16.67%) chance of dodging an attack, which inflicts the Cerebral Mindtrick debuff on them for four seconds.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info4: Despite being a debuff, it increases critical strike chance and summon damage by 10%.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info5: While the debuff is active, the player cannot dodge another attack.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.info6: The Brain of Confusion is always dropped from the Brain of Cthulhu's Treasure Bag in Expert Mode.
item.confluence.brain_of_confusion.toolt: Has a chance to create illusions and dodge an attack
Temporarily increase critical chance after dodge
May confuse nearby enemies after being struck
item.confluence.bundle_of_balloons.info: The Bundle of Balloons is an accessory that allows the wearer to perform a quadruple jump, as well as increasing the player's jump duration by 33% and jump speed by 30%.
item.confluence.bundle_of_balloons.info2: Each of the jumps has an effect from the different combined items: sandstorm jump, then blizzard jump, then cloud jump.
item.confluence.bundle_of_balloons.info3: Crafting this item requires three of the variants of Cloud in a Balloon, which in turn requires a total of 3 Shiny Red Balloons.
item.confluence.bundle_of_balloons.toolt: Allows the holder to quadruple jump
item.confluence.bundle_of_horseshoe_ball: Allows the holder to quadruple jump
Increases jump height and negates fall damage
The Bundle of Horseshoe Balloons is an accessory which combines the functionalities of the Bundle of Balloons and the Lucky Horseshoe.
When equipped, it allows the wearer to perform a quadruple jump, as well as increasing the player's jump duration by 33%, jump speed by 30%, and luck by 0.05.
Each of the jumps has an effect from the different combined items: sandstorm jump, then blizzard jump, then cloud jump. Having it equipped also prevents the player from taking fall damage.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info: The Celestial Cuffs are a pre-Hardmode accessory which restores mana when the wearer is damaged and increases pickup range for Stars.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info2: It also increases maximum mana by 20.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info3: Mana restored is equal to the damage of the attack before factoring defense and damage reduction effects.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info4: Damage from drowning and debuffs does not trigger this effect, while fall damage will.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info5: This effect does not stack with the mana restoration effect of the Magic Cuffs.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info6: The mana star pickup range is increased by 18.75 tiles, for a total of 21.375 tiles.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.info7: This effect does not stack with the pickup range increase effect of the Celestial Magnet, Magnet Flower or Celestial Emblem.
item.confluence.celestial_cuffs.tooltip: Increases the pickup range of Mana Stars
item.confluence.celestial_emblem.info: The Celestial Emblem is a Hardmode accessory that offers 15% increased magic damage and a 18.75-tile increased pickup range for Stars (21.375 tile total range).
item.confluence.celestial_emblem.tooltip: Increases the pickup range of Mana Stars
item.confluence.celestial_magnet.info: The Celestial Magnet is an accessory that greatly increases the pickup range for Stars.
item.confluence.celestial_magnet.info2: The increase in pickup range is 18.75 tiles, extending the base range of 2.625 tiles to 21.375 tiles.
item.confluence.celestial_magnet.info3: This effect does not stack with that of any of the Celestial Magnet's upgrades.
item.confluence.celestial_magnet.info4: The Celestial Magnet has a 1/4 (25%) of being found inside Skyware Chests on Floating Islands, as well as a 1/4 (25%) chance of being obtained from Sky Crates and Azure Crates.
item.confluence.celestial_magnet.tooltip: Increases the pickup range of Mana Stars
item.confluence.celestial_stone.info: The Celestial Stone is a Hardmode post-Golem accessory crafted from a Moon Stone and a Sun Stone at the Tinkerer's Workshop.
item.confluence.celestial_stone.info2: It offers the same boosts as its components do, and as such, it is active during both day and night.
item.confluence.celestial_stone.info3: It can be combined with the Moon Shell to form a Celestial Shell。
item.confluence.charm_of_myths.info: The Charm of Myths is a Hardmode accessory which combines the effects of Band of Regeneration and Philosopher's Stone.
item.confluence.charm_of_myths.info2: When equipped, it regenerates 1 health every second and decreases the Potion Sickness debuff duration by 25%.
item.confluence.charm_of_myths.info3: Therefore, 45 seconds after consuming a recovery potion while the Charm of Myths is equipped, another one can be consumed.
item.confluence.charm_of_myths.tooltip: Provides health regeneration and reduces the cooldown of healing potions
item.confluence.climbing_claws.tooltip: Improved ability if combined with Shoe Spikes
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_balloon.info: The Cloud in a Balloon is an accessory that combines the functionality of the Cloud in a Bottle and the Shiny Red Balloon.
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_balloon.info2: It boosts jump height by 33%, and jump speed by 30%, increasing the player's first jump's height to 10.5 blocks (~75% increase), and provides a double jump that hits 9 blocks, for a total height of 19.5 blocks.
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_balloon.info3: Jump height is oddly reduced when underwater, reducing your total underwater height from 15 blocks (8 + 7 from Cloud jump) to 13 blocks (7 + 6 from Cloud jump).
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_bottle.info: The Cloud in a Bottle is an accessory that can be found in Gold Chests in the Underground and Cavern layers.
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_bottle.info2: When equipped, it allows the player an extra jump.
item.confluence.cloud_in_a_bottle.info3: The extra jump has a 75% jump duration compared to a normal jump, increasing the maximum height the player can reach without other accessories by 5 tiles, for a total of 11 tiles.
item.confluence.cobalt_shield.info: The Cobalt Shield is a pre-Hardmode shield accessory that grants the player immunity to knockback when equipped, and also provides 1 defense.
item.confluence.cobalt_shield.info2: The Cobalt Shield has a 1/7 (14.29%) chance of being obtained from the Locked Gold Chests found in the Dungeon, as well as a 1/7 (14.29%) chance of being obtained from Golden Lock Boxes.
item.confluence.coin_ring.info: The Coin Ring is a Hardmode accessory created by other accessories exclusively dropped from pirate enemies during Pirate Invasion.
item.confluence.coin_ring.info2: It combines the effect of Gold Ring and Lucky Coin, which increases the pickup range for coins, and causes enemies to occasionally drop 1 to 10 more coins when hit and grants +0.05 luck.
item.confluence.coin_ring.tooltip: Increasing the coin pickup range and hitting enemies will sometimes drop additional coins
item.confluence.compass.info: The Compass is an informational accessory that enables an on-screen display of the player's lateral position when equipped.
item.confluence.compass.info2: Position is shown in the number of feet (1 foot = 1/2 tile) to the East or West of the center of the map.
item.confluence.compass.info3: The centerpoint of the map is usually very close to the initial spawn point.
item.confluence.compass.info4: The Compass has a 1/83 (1.2%) chance of being dropped by Crawdads, Giant Shellies, and Salamanders, a 1/75 (1.33%) chance to be dropped by Piranhas, and a 1/50 (2%) chance to be dropped by Mother Slimes, Snow Flinxes, Undead Vikings, and Armored Vikings.
item.confluence.compass.info5: The Compass is one of the three parts necessary to make the GPS, with the others being the Depth Meter and the Gold Watch or Platinum Watch, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.copper_watch.info: When equipped in an accessory slot or simply held in the inventory, a clock will appear in the upper-right corner of the playing screen, revealing the in-game time accurate to the last hour.
item.confluence.copper_watch.info2: An hour of Terraria game time is equivalent to one minute of real-world time. The Copper Watch can be used to craft the 5 Second Timer.
item.confluence.countercurse_mantra.info: The Countercurse Mantra is an immunity accessory that combines the functions of the Megaphone and the Nazar.
This item grants immunity to both the Silenced and Cursed debuffs.
It is one of the ingredients required to make the Ankh Charm, which is further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.cross_necklace.info: The Cross Necklace is a Hardmode accessory that doubles the duration of the invincibility a player is afforded after taking damage, from about 0.67 seconds to about 1.33 seconds.
item.confluence.cross_necklace.info2: The Cross Necklace has a 1/6 (16.67%) chance to be dropped by Mimics.
item.confluence.cross_necklace.tooltip: Increases TOTAL_LENGTH of invincibility after taking damage
item.confluence.demon_heart.tooltip: Permanently increases the number of accessory slots
item.confluence.depth_meter.info: The Depth Meter is an informational accessory that displays the player's depth.
item.confluence.depth_meter.info2: Depth is relative to the boundary between the Surface and Underground layers, which has a depth of 0 and is displayed as "Level".
item.confluence.depth_meter.info3: The display shows the vertical distance to this line and the name of the current layer. Depth is always measured at the level of the player's feet.
item.confluence.depth_meter.info4: The Depth Meter is one of the three parts necessary to make the GPS, with the others being the Compass and the Gold Watch or Platinum Watch, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.destroyer_emblem.info: The Destroyer Emblem is a Hardmode, post-Golem accessory that gives the player 10% increased damage and 8% increased critical strike chance.
item.confluence.dps_meter.info: The DPS Meter is an informational accessory that displays the DPS of the weapon that last dealt damage to any entity, including NPCs, Target Dummies, critters, and other players.
item.confluence.dps_meter.info2: The DPS Meter is one of the three parts necessary to make the Goblin Tech, with the others being the Metal Detector and the Stopwatch, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.info: The Dunerider Boots are an accessory that increases the player's maximum movement speed. The Dunerider Boots have a 1/7 (14.29%) chance of being found in Sandstone Chests in the Underground Desert and a 1/8 (12.5%) chance of being found in Oasis Crates and Mirage Crates obtained from fishing in the Oasis.
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.info2: When equipped, it grants the following bonuses:
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.info3: Increases the player's maximum movement speed to 22.5 tiles/second (31 mph)
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.info4: When moving on any Sand, Sandstone, or Hardened Sand, increases maximum movement speed by 15% (to 39.38 tiles/second or 54 mph by default) and increases acceleration and deceleration by 75%, from 0.3 tiles/second² to 0.525 tiles/second² and from 0.75 tiles/second² to 1.3125 tiles/second², respectively
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.tooltip: The wearer can run super fast, and even faster on sand
item.confluence.dunerider_boots.tooltip2: 'Walk without rhythm and you won't attract the worm'
item.confluence.extendo_grip.info: The Extendo Grip is an accessory that extends block mining and placement reach by 3 tiles horizontally and 2 tiles vertically.
item.confluence.eye_of_the_golem.info: The Eye of the Golem is a Hardmode, post-Golem accessory that grants +10% critical strike chance.
item.confluence.eye_of_the_golem.info2: It has a 1/7 (14.29%) chance of being dropped by Golem.
item.confluence.fairy_boots.info: Fairy Boots are an accessory that are made from the Spectre Boots and Flower Boots at a Tinkerer's Workshop.
item.confluence.fairy_boots.info2: They combine both effects into one pair of boots.
item.confluence.fart_in_a_balloon.info: The Fart in a Balloon is an accessory that combines the effects of the Fart in a Jar and the Shiny Red Balloon.
item.confluence.fart_in_a_balloon.info2: It boosts jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing the player's first jump's height to ~10.5 blocks (~75% increase), and provides a double jump that goes to 18.5 blocks, for a total of 29 blocks.
item.confluence.fart_in_a_balloon.info3: Unlike most other double-jump balloons, the Fart in a Balloon's full jump is high enough for the player to take minor fall damage, unless the player has fall damage immunity accessories like the Lucky Horseshoe. The double jump also makes a fart sound.
item.confluence.fart_in_a_jar.info: The Fart in a Jar is an accessory that allows the player to perform a double jump, accompanied by a farting sound effect.
item.confluence.fart_in_a_jar.info2: The Fart jump goes 10.5 tiles into the air, totalling 16.5 tiles when put together with the first jump.
item.confluence.fast_clock.info: The Fast Clock is a Hardmode immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Slow debuff.
item.confluence.fast_clock.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Pixies, Mummies, and Wraiths.
item.confluence.fast_clock.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make The Plan, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.feral_claws.info: Feral Claws are an accessory that increases melee attack speed by 12%, and stacks with all other attack speed boosts.
item.confluence.feral_claws.info2: Feral Claws can be found in Jungle Crates, Bramble Crates, and Ivy Chests located in Jungle Shrines and at the base of a Living Mahogany Tree in the Underground Jungle.
item.confluence.feral_claws.info3: In addition to increasing melee attack speed, Feral Claws give autoswing to all melee weapons and Whips.
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.info: The Fire Gauntlet is a Hardmode accessory that boosts melee weapons in the following ways:
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.info2: Both the weapon sprite and projectile emit orange light particles that gives off light
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.info3: They cause the Hellfire debuff (does not apply in PvP)
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.info7: They gain autoswing (also applies to whips)
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.info9: The Fire Gauntlet is only available after defeating all three mechanical bosses.
item.confluence.fire_gauntlet.tooltip: Increases melee knockback and melee attacks inflict fire damage
item.confluence.fish_finder.info: The Fish Finder is an informational accessory that provides the information displayed by the Fisherman's Pocket Guide, which displays the player's current fishing power.
The Fisherman's Pocket Guide is an informational accessory that displays the player's current Fishing Power. The Fisherman's Pocket Guide can be received as a 1/34 (2.94%)[1] chance reward for completing a fishing quest for the Angler NPC, depending on the number of completed quests and other factors (for details, see Angler).

The Fisherman's Pocket Guide is one of the three parts necessary to make the Fish Finder, with the others being the Sextant and the Weather Radio, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.fishing_bobber.info: Fishing Bobbers are accessories that change the appearance of a fishing pole's bobber and increase the player's Fishing Power by 10.
item.confluence.fledgling_wings.info: The Fledgling Wings are the only pre-Hardmode wings.
item.confluence.fledgling_wings.info2: Like all wings, they grant the player the ability to fly and glide when equipped, as well as not take fall damage.
item.confluence.fledgling_wings.info3: At top speed, they allow traveling at 15 mph horizontally and 22 mph vertically.
item.confluence.fledgling_wings.info4: They have a flight time of 1.25 seconds and a vertical speed multiplier of 150%.
item.confluence.fledgling_wings.info5: The Fledgling Wings can be obtained from Skyware Chests on Floating Islands, as well as Sky Crates and Azure Crates from fishing.
item.confluence.flesh_knuckles.info: Flesh Knuckles are a Hardmode accessory. They increase the player's defense by 8 and aggro by 400.
item.confluence.flesh_knuckles.info2: Flesh Knuckles have a 1/5 (20%) chance to be dropped by Crimson Mimics.
item.confluence.flippers.info: The Flipper is an accessory that allows a player to swim in liquid.
item.confluence.flippers.info2: With the Flipper equipped in an accessory slot, the player can swim upwards in Water, Lava, or Honey, by holding or pressing Jump Key repeatedly — essentially allowing unlimited multi-jumps while within liquid.
item.confluence.flippers.info3: It can be found in Water Chests and Ocean/Seaside Crates.
item.confluence.flower_boots.info: Flower Boots are a rare accessory which cause flowers to grow when the player walks on regular, Jungle, Hallowed, and Ash grass.
item.confluence.flower_boots.info2: These flowers are functionally the same as the tall weeds that grow naturally on grass, and drop Seeds and Hay normally.
item.confluence.flower_boots.info3: Wearing Flower Boots drastically decreases the chance of critters spawning from destroyed tall grass and plants.
item.confluence.flower_boots.info4: Flower Boots can occasionally be found in Ivy Chests, Jungle Crates and Bramble Crates.
item.confluence.flower_boots.tooltip: Flowers grow on the grass you walk on
item.confluence.flurry_boots.info: Flurry Boots are an accessory that can be found in Frozen Chests in the underground Snow Biome, as well as Frozen and Boreal Crates.
item.confluence.flurry_boots.info2: When equipped, they allow the player to gain a speed boost after running for a certain distance continuously.
item.confluence.flurry_boots.info3: Your speed will continue increasing until maximum speed is attained.
item.confluence.flurry_boots.info4: In the case of the Flurry Boots, the user will leave a short dust trail under themselves as they run, which disappears immediately upon stopping, unlike the Hermes Boots.
item.confluence.frog_flipper.info: The Frog Flipper is an accessory crafted from a Frog Leg and a Flipper.
item.confluence.frog_flipper.info2: It combines the abilities of these two items, increasing the player's jump speed and safe falling distance, allowing auto-jump, and giving the player the ability to swim.
item.confluence.frog_leg.info: The Frog Leg is an accessory that can be fished in any viable body of water. It aids jumping in the following ways:
item.confluence.frog_leg.info2: Increases the player's jump speed by 1.6.
item.confluence.frog_leg.info3: The player automatically jumps while the Jump key is held. This effect also works with Climbing Claws and other climbing accessories.
item.confluence.frog_leg.info4: Increases the maximum safe falling distance by 10
item.confluence.frog_leg.info5: These effects also apply with wings equipped.
item.confluence.frostspark_boots.info: The Frostspark Boots are an accessory crafted by combining Lightning Boots and Ice Skates together at a Tinkerer's Workshop.
item.confluence.frostspark_boots.info2: It provides the benefits of both. They also have an 8% increased movement speed.
item.confluence.frostspark_boots.info3: Frostspark Boots display a different particle effect than the Spectre Boots or Lightning Boots: they produce snow clouds similar to those made by the Blizzard in a Bottle.
item.confluence.frostspark_boots.tooltip: Allows flight, super fast running, and extra mobility on ice
item.confluence.frozen_shield.info: The Frozen Shield is a Hardmode, post-Plantera shield accessory that combines the functionalities of the Paladin's Shield and the Frozen Turtle Shell:
item.confluence.frozen_shield.info2: It redirects some damage done to teammates to the player, increases defense by 6, grants immunity to knockback, and provides the player with a damage-absorbing shield when they are at low health.
item.confluence.frozen_shield.tooltip: Absorbs 25% of damage done to players on your team when above 25% life
item.confluence.frozen_shield.tooltip2: Puts a shell around the owner when below 50% life that reduces damage by 25%
item.confluence.frozen_turtle_shell.info: The Frozen Turtle Shell is a Hardmode accessory that grants the Ice Barrier buff when equipped,
Gives 25% damage reduction as long as their health remains at or below 50%.
The Frozen Turtle Shell has a 1/50 (2%) chance of being dropped by Ice Tortoises in the Ice biome.
item.confluence.frozen_turtle_shell.tool: Puts a shell around the owner when below 50% life that reduces damage by 25%
item.confluence.glowing_fishing_bobber.t: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.goblin_tech.info: The Goblin Tech is an informational accessory, and is a combination of the Stopwatch, DPS Meter, and Metal Detector, displaying the most valuable nearby item, your current DPS, and your speed.
item.confluence.goblin_tech.info2: The Stopwatch and DPS Meter are sold by the Traveling Merchant, while the Metal Detector is dropped by the Nymph.
item.confluence.gold_ring.info: The Gold Ring is a Hardmode accessory that greatly increases the pickup range for coins.
item.confluence.gold_ring.info2: It has a 1/500 (0.2%) chance to be dropped by pirates (except Parrots) during Pirate Invasions, with a 1/125 (0.8%) chance from the Pirate Captain.
item.confluence.gold_ring.info3: It also has a 1/15 (6.67%) chance to be dropped by the Flying Dutchman.
item.confluence.gold_ring.info4: The increase in pickup range is 21.875 tiles, extending the base range of 2.625 tiles to 24.5 tiles.
item.confluence.gold_ring.info5: This effect does not stack with that of any of the Gold Ring's upgrades.
item.confluence.gold_watch.info: The Gold Watch is a high-tier watch.
item.confluence.gold_watch.info2: When equipped in an accessory slot or simply held in the inventory, a clock will appear in the upper-right corner of the playing screen, revealing the in-game time accurate to the last minute.
item.confluence.gold_watch.info3: The Gold Watch (or Platinum Watch) is one of the three parts necessary to make the GPS, with the others being the Compass and the Depth Meter, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.gold_watch.info4: The Gold Watch can also be used to craft the 1 Second Timer.
item.confluence.gps.info: The GPS is an informational accessory that enables an on-screen display of the player's current depth, lateral position, and time.
item.confluence.gravity_globe.info: The Gravity Globe is a Hardmode, post-Moon Lord accessory that allows the holder to flip gravity, so that the player falls up instead of down, and toggle gravity back to normal afterward. Once equipped, pressing the Up key toggles the gravity direction.
item.confluence.gravity_globe.info2: This only affects the player with the item equipped. The Gravity Globe is always dropped from the Moon Lord's Treasure Bag in Expert Mode.
item.confluence.gravity_globe.tooltip: Allows the holder to reverse gravity
The Green Horseshoe Balloon is an accessory that grants immunity to fall damage, increases jump height by 33%, jump speed by 30%, grants a double jump, and grants +0.05 luck.

The height of the first jump is increased from 6 blocks to 10.5 blocks (~75% increase), while the double jump's height is increased from 10.5 blocks to 18.5 blocks, reaching a total of 29 blocks with both jumps.
The double jump also makes a fart sound.
Jump height is oddly reduced when underwater, to 18 blocks (7 blocks + ~11 blocks from Fart jump).
item.confluence.hand_of_creation.tooltip: Decreased 'Right Click Delay' by 3, cannot stack the decrease of its material
item.confluence.hand_warmer.info: The Hand Warmer is an immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Chilled and Frozen debuffs.
item.confluence.hand_warmer.info2: It is obtained from Presents, with a chance of 0.62% in pre-Hardmode and 0.58% in Hardmode.
item.confluence.hand_warmer.tooltip: Provides immunity to chill and freezing effects
item.confluence.helium_moss_fishing_bobb: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info: Hermes Boots are an accessory that can be found in Chests in the Underground and Cavern layers.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info10: All four listed boots are interchangeable when crafting Spectre Boots.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info2: When equipped, they allow the player to gain a movement speed boost after running for a certain distance continuously.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info3: The speed will continue increasing until maximum speed is attained.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info4: At full sprint, they will increase the player's horizontal movement speed to 30 mph.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info5: However, if the player runs into a wall without autojumping, the player will stop and have to speed up again.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info6: (See Sprinting accessories for more information on the sprint effect).
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info7: The Hermes Boots, Flurry Boots, and the Sailfish Boots have identical functionality, with their only differences being aesthetic.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info8: In the case of the Hermes Boots, the user will leave a lasting trail of small dust clouds as they run, which persists for a few seconds.
item.confluence.hermes_boots.info9: The Dunerider Boots function similarly, but additionally grant an even larger boost on sand.
item.confluence.hero_shield.info: The Hero Shield is a Hardmode post-Plantera shield accessory that redirects 25% of damage from players on the same team while above 25% health, similar to the effect of the Paladin's Shield.
item.confluence.hero_shield.info2: Furthermore, it increases defense by 10, increases aggro by 400, and grants immunity to knockback.
item.confluence.high_test_fishing_line.i: The High Test Fishing Line is an accessory that prevents fishing line from breaking while fishing when equipped.
Without the High Test Fishing Line equipped, there is a 1/7 (14.29%) chance that the line will break on any reel-in that was supposed to yield a catch.
item.confluence.hive_pack.info: The Hive Pack is a pre-Hardmode accessory that, when equipped, grants a 1/2 (50%) chance of replacing friendly Bee projectiles with larger "Giant Bees".
item.confluence.hive_pack.info2: The Hive Pack is always dropped from the Queen Bee's Treasure Bag in Expert Mode.
item.confluence.hive_pack.tooltip: Increases the strength of friendly bees
item.confluence.honey_balloon.info: The Honey Balloon is an accessory that combines the functions of a Shiny Red Balloon and a Honey Comb.
item.confluence.honey_balloon.info2: It boosts jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing your first jump's height to ~10½ blocks (~75% increase), while oddly reducing it when underwater, from 8 blocks-to 7 blocks, and releases a small swarm of angry bees when the player is hurt, which seek out and deal small amounts of damage to enemies.
item.confluence.honey_comb.info: The Honey Comb is a pre-Hardmode accessory which, when equipped, spawns 1–3 (or 1–4 with a Hive Pack equipped) bee projectiles which attack nearby enemies each time the player takes damage.
item.confluence.honey_comb.info2: It also grants the Honey buff for 5 seconds after being damaged.
item.confluence.honey_comb.info3: The Honey Comb has a 1/3 (33.33%) chance to be dropped by the Queen Bee.
item.confluence.honey_comb.tooltip: Releases bees and douses the user in honey when damaged
item.confluence.horseshoe_balloon.toolti: Increases jump height and negates fall damage
item.confluence.ice_skates.info: Ice Skates are a pre-Hardmode accessory that improves a player's movement control on Thin Ice, all Ice Blocks, Ice Rod blocks, Frozen Slime Blocks and Aetherium Blocks.
item.confluence.ice_skates.info2: The player accelerates faster, slides shorter distances, and will no longer cause Thin Ice to break when landing from falls or jumps.
item.confluence.ice_skates.info3: Ice Skates have a 1551/10000 (15.51%) chance of being found inside Frozen Chests in the Ice biome, as well as a 1/6 (16.67%) chance of being obtained from Frozen and Boreal Crates.
item.confluence.ice_skates.tooltip2: Ice will not break when you fall on it
item.confluence.krypton_moss_fishing_bob: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.lava_charm.info: The Lava Charm is an accessory that grants immunity to lava for 7 seconds. It is found in Chests located in the cavern layer as well as obtained from Hellstone Crates and Obsidian Crates with a 1/20 (5%) chance.
item.confluence.lava_charm.info2: it can only be found in Chests in the lower portion of the Caverns where lava pools can naturally spawn, as opposed to Chests throughout the entirety of the Caverns.
item.confluence.lava_charm.info3: When the Lava Charm is equipped and the player comes into contact with lava, a 7-second countdown begins, signified by a lava meter that displays over the player's head.
item.confluence.lava_charm.info4: It operates similarly to the breath meter, but displays flame icons instead of bubbles.
item.confluence.lava_charm.info5: Lava immunity time is recharged gradually by exiting lava, the same way breathing time is recharged by exiting water (albeit much more slowly).
item.confluence.lava_moss_fishing_bobber: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.lava_waders.info: The Lava Waders are an accessory that allow the player to walk on the surface of all liquids, including water, honey, shimmer and even lava, without taking lava damage or triggering the On Fire! debuff (unlike the Water Walking Boots and Obsidian Water Walking Boots, which only allow walking on water and honey).
item.confluence.lava_waders.info2: Lava Waders also allow the player to submerge in lava safely for 7 seconds (press the Down key to submerge), without incurring lava damage or triggering the On Fire! debuff.
item.confluence.lava_waders.info3: The 7-second countdown is signified by a lava meter that displays over the player's head, similar to the Breath meter, but displaying flame icons instead of bubbles.
item.confluence.lava_waders.info4: Lava immunity time is recharged gradually by exiting lava, the same way breathing time is recharged by exiting water (albeit much more slowly).
item.confluence.lava_waders.info5: All liquids, including lava, can be walked on indefinitely while the Lava Waders are equipped.
item.confluence.lava_waders.info6: The countdown only applies when submerged in lava, whereas the player can stand on its surface indefinitely.
item.confluence.lava_waders.info7: Lava Waders additionally provide immunity to the Burning debuff incurred from contact with Meteorite, Hellstone or Hellstone Brick.
item.confluence.lava_waders.info8: It also reduces lava's base damage from 80 to 35.
item.confluence.lava_waders.tooltip2: Grants immunity to fire blocks and 7 seconds of immunity to lava
item.confluence.lavaproof_fishing_hook.i: The Lavaproof Fishing Hook is an accessory that can be found in Obsidian Crates and Hellstone Crates, both of which can be obtained from fishing in lava.
When equipped, it allows the player to catch fish in lava with any bait and any fishing pole.
item.confluence.lavaproof_fishing_hook.t: Allows fishing in lava regardless of bait or rod used.
item.confluence.lavaproof_tackle_bag.inf: The Lavaproof Tackle Bag is an accessory that combines the functionalities of its components:

The Angler Earring's 10% boost to fishing power, the Tackle Box's chance not to consume bait, the unbreakable quality of the High Test Fishing Line, and the ability to fish in lava from the Lavaproof Fishing Hook.
The Lavaproof Tackle Bag's increase in fishing power stacks with that of the Angler Earring and the Angler Tackle Bag, granting a total boost of 30% if all three are equipped.
The decreased chance to consume bait does not stack with that of the Tackle Box or the Angler Tackle Bag.
item.confluence.lavaproof_tackle_bag.too: Allows fishing in lava regardless of bait or rod used.
Line never breaks and −5% bait consumption chance
item.confluence.life_form_analyzer.info: The Lifeform Analyzer is an informational accessory that displays the name of rare enemies, critters, and undiscovered NPCs (see list below) within 81.25 tiles around the player.
item.confluence.life_form_analyzer.info2: The Lifeform Analyzer is one of the three parts necessary to make the R.E.K. 3000, with the others being the Tally Counter and the Radar, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.lightning_boots.info: Lightning Boots are an accessory that have essentially the same functionality as Spectre Boots, but with enhanced running speed.
item.confluence.lightning_boots.info2: Its visual effects do not differ from the Spectre Boots.
item.confluence.lightning_boots.info3: They have an 8% movement speed bonus compared to the Spectre Boots.
item.confluence.lucky_coin.info: The Lucky Coin is an extremely rare Hardmode accessory that causes enemies to drop extra coins when damaged and grants the player +0.05 luck.
item.confluence.lucky_coin.info2: It has a  1/2000 (0.05%) chance to be dropped by pirates (except Parrots) during Pirate Invasions, with a  1/500 (0.2%) chance from the Pirate Captain.
item.confluence.lucky_coin.info3: It also has a 1/15 (6.67%) chance to be dropped by the Flying Dutchman.
item.confluence.lucky_coin.info4: With the Lucky Coin equipped, there is a 1/5 (20%) chance that 1 to 10 extra coins will drop each time the player damages an enemy.
item.confluence.lucky_coin.info5: Each time extra coins drop, the following probabilities determine the coin type:
item.confluence.lucky_coin.tooltip: Hitting an enemy can sometimes drop extra coins
item.confluence.lucky_horseshoe.info: The Lucky Horseshoe is an accessory that negates fall damage and grants +0.05 luck.
item.confluence.lucky_horseshoe.info2: The Lucky Horseshoe has a 1/4 (25%) of being found inside Skyware Chests on Floating Islands, as well as a 1/4 (25%) chance of being obtained from Sky Crates and Azure Crates.
item.confluence.lucky_horseshoe.tooltip: 'Said to bring good fortune and keep evil spirits at bay'
item.confluence.magic_cuffs.info: The Magic Cuffs are a pre-Hardmode accessory which increases maximum mana by 20 and restores mana when the wearer is damaged.
item.confluence.magic_cuffs.info2: Mana restored is equal to the damage of the attack before factoring defense and damage reduction effects.
item.confluence.magic_cuffs.info3: Damage from drowning and debuffs does not trigger this effect, while damage from falling will.
item.confluence.magic_cuffs.info4: This effect does not stack with the mana restoration effect of the Celestial Cuffs.
item.confluence.magic_quiver.tooltip: Increases arrow damage by 10% and greatly increases arrow speed
item.confluence.magiluminescence.info: The Magiluminescence is a pre-Hardmode accessory that increases the player's maximum movement speed by 15% and their acceleration and deceleration by 75%.
item.confluence.magiluminescence.info2: This increase stacks with the bonus of the Hermes Boots and their variants.
item.confluence.magiluminescence.info3: It also creates an aura of light around the player, which can be useful when exploring underground.
item.confluence.magiluminescence.info4: The Magiluminescence's movement speed buffs are disabled when the player is not grounded.
item.confluence.magiluminescence.tooltip: 'A brief light in my dark life.'
item.confluence.magma_skull.info: The Magma Skull is a pre-Hardmode immunity accessory that grants the player immunity from blocks that inflict the Burning debuff and grants immunity to lava for 7 seconds.
item.confluence.magma_skull.info2: The Magma Skull can also be worn in a Social Accessory Slot as a vanity head item.
item.confluence.magma_skull.tooltip: Immunity to fire blocks, melee attacks deal fire damage
item.confluence.magma_stone.info: The Magma Stone is an accessory that drops from Lava Bats (2% chance) and Hellbats (0.67% chance) in The Underworld.
item.confluence.magma_stone.info2: It causes the wearer's melee attacks to inflict the Hellfire debuff on enemies, and also add orange flame particles effect on both the weapon sprite and their projectile that gives off light.
item.confluence.magma_stone.info3: The duration of the debuff is random, and varies according to the table on the right.
item.confluence.magnet_flower.info: The Magnet Flower is an accessory that reduces mana usage by 8%, automatically uses Mana Potions when needed, and increases pickup range for Stars by 18.75 tiles.
item.confluence.magnet_flower.info2: It will use the first available Mana Potion in the player's inventory when out of mana (from left to right and top to bottom).
item.confluence.magnet_flower.info3: The Magnet Flower has the exact same functional effects of both its component items.
item.confluence.magnet_flower.tooltip2: Automatically uses mana potions when needed
item.confluence.magnet_flower.tooltip3: Increases the pickup range of Mana Stars
item.confluence.mana_cloak.info: The Mana Cloak is a Hardmode accessory that combines the effects of the Mana Flower and Star Cloak. It also adds a new effect to the stars spawned by the Star Cloak.
item.confluence.mana_cloak.info2: It also adds a new effect to the stars spawned by the Star Cloak.
item.confluence.mana_cloak.info3: When the player takes damage, the Mana Cloak will spawn three stars that damage enemies.
item.confluence.mana_cloak.info4: The mana star will disappear 5 seconds after it is spawned if not picked up.
item.confluence.mana_cloak.info5: Note that only one mana-restoring star can spawn per second, no matter how many times the Mana Cloak is triggered.
item.confluence.mana_flower.info: The Mana Flower is a pre-Hardmode accessory that reduces mana usage by 8%, and enables auto-consumption of any mana-restoring potions in the player's inventory when mana is depleted.
item.confluence.mana_flower.info2: The Mana Flower stacks with other mana cost-reduction items, including Nature's Gift. It is crafted at the Tinkerer's Workshop.
item.confluence.mana_flower.tooltip2: Automatically uses mana potions when needed
item.confluence.mana_regeneration_band.i: The Mana Regeneration Band is an accessory item made by combining a Band of Starpower and a Band of Regeneration at a Tinkerer's Workshop.
It somewhat combines the effects of both bands, increasing a player's maximum mana and converting the bonus health regeneration provided by the Band of Regeneration into mana regeneration.
item.confluence.mechanical_glove.info: The Mechanical Glove is a Hardmode accessory that doubles all melee weapons' knockback, and increases melee damage and speed by 12%.
item.confluence.mechanical_glove.info2: It is only available after defeating all mechanical bosses.
item.confluence.mechanical_glove.info3: The Mechanical Glove enables autoswing for all melee weapons and whips and increases their size by 10%.
item.confluence.mechanical_lens.info: The Mechanical Lens is an informational accessory which will reveal placed wires and actuators.
item.confluence.mechanical_lens.info2: Each color of wire can be shown at maximum brightness, regular, or faded, which is configurable by the toggles.
item.confluence.medicated_bandage.info: The Medicated Bandage is an immunity accessory that combines the functions of the Adhesive Bandage and the Bezoar.
item.confluence.medicated_bandage.info2: This item grants immunity to any Bleeding and Poison debuffs.
item.confluence.medicated_bandage.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Ankh Charm, which is further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.megaphone.info: The Megaphone is an immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Silenced debuff.
item.confluence.megaphone.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Pixies, Green Jellyfish, Dark Mummies, and Blood Mummies.
item.confluence.megaphone.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Countercurse Mantra, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.metal_detector.info: The Metal Detector is an informational accessory that detects valuable objects, including ores, chests, Life Crystals, and Life Fruit, within a rectangular area of 170×125[1] tiles centered on the player.
item.confluence.metal_detector.info2: The Metal Detector has a 1/2 (50%) / 100% chance of being dropped by Nymphs, a rare cavern enemy.
item.confluence.metal_detector.info3: The Metal Detector displays the specific type of what was detected, for instance, "Chlorophyte detected nearby!" When multiple valuables are detected, only the one with the highest value is noted.
item.confluence.metal_detector.info4: Like most informational accessories, it does not directly reveal the location or direction of the detected object.
item.confluence.metal_detector.info5: The Metal Detector is one of the three parts necessary to make the Goblin Tech, with the others being the Stopwatch and the DPS Meter, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info: The Molten Charm is a pre-Hardmode accessory crafted from a Lava Charm and an Obsidian Skull, combining the effects of both items.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info2: When the Molten Charm is equipped and the player comes into contact with lava, a 7-second countdown begins, signified by a lava meter that displays over the player's head.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info3: It operates similarly to the Breath meter, but displays flame icons instead of bubbles.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info4: Lava immunity time is recharged gradually by exiting lava, the same way breathing time is recharged by exiting water (albeit much more slowly).
item.confluence.molten_charm.info5: The Molten Charm also grants immunity to the burning damage normally inflicted by contact with Meteorite, Hellstone, and Hellstone Brick.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info6: It does not grant immunity to other fire-based damage.
item.confluence.molten_charm.info7: This accessory can be combined with the Water Walking Boots or the Obsidian Water Walking Boots, which are used in crafting the Lava Waders.
item.confluence.molten_skull_rose.info: The Molten Skull Rose is an accessory that represents the final upgrade of the Obsidian Skull.
item.confluence.molten_skull_rose.info2: It grants 7 seconds of immunity to lava, immunity from fire blocks, and reduces damage taken from lava.
item.confluence.molten_skull_rose.info3: When worn, the item can be seen on the players head.
item.confluence.molten_skull_rose.info4: This item can also be crafted in three different ways.
item.confluence.moon_stone.info: The Moon Stone is a Hardmode accessory which has a 1/35 (2.86%) / 69/1225 (5.63%) chance to drop from Vampires during the Solar Eclipse event.
item.confluence.moon_stone.info2: It grants the same stat bonuses as the Sun Stone, but these bonuses will only activate during the night or during a Solar Eclipse.
item.confluence.natures_gift.info: Nature's Gift is an accessory that reduces the mana cost of using magic weapons and other mana-consuming items by 6%.
item.confluence.natures_gift.info2: It is acquired by harvesting a rare flower that grows on Jungle grass in the Underground Jungle, using any weapon or tool. The flower appears as a blue version of the Jungle Rose.
item.confluence.nazar.info: The Nazar is a post-Skeletron immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Cursed debuff.
item.confluence.nazar.info2: It has a 1/100 (1%) / 1/50 (2%) chance to drop from Cursed Skulls, Giant Cursed Skulls, Cursed Hammers, Crimson Axes, and Enchanted Swords.
item.confluence.nazar.info3: It is one of the ingredients of the Countercurse Mantra, which is a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory which can be further crafted into the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.neon_moss_fishing_bobber: Increases fishing power,Your bobber now glows
item.confluence.obsidian_horseshoe.info: The Obsidian Horseshoe is an accessory that combines the functionality of the Lucky Horseshoe and the Obsidian Skull.
item.confluence.obsidian_horseshoe.info2: It grants immunity to the burning damage inflicted by Meteorite, Hellstone, and Hellstone Bricks, negates fall damage and grants +0.05 luck.
item.confluence.obsidian_horseshoe.info3: However, it does not provide the extra 1 point of defense that is granted by the Obsidian Skull.
item.confluence.obsidian_rose.info: The Obsidian Rose is an accessory that reduces the base damage taken from lava from 80 to 35 and halves the duration of the On Fire! debuff inflicted by it from 7 / 14 / 17.5 seconds to 3.5 / 7 / 8.75 seconds.
item.confluence.obsidian_rose.info2: It has a 1/20 (5%) chance of being dropped by Fire Imps, an enemy found in The Underworld.
item.confluence.obsidian_shield.info: The Obsidian Shield is a shield accessory made from the Cobalt Shield and Obsidian Skull, and combines their functionality as well as their defense boosts.
item.confluence.obsidian_shield.info2: It grants immunity from knockback, as well as immunity from the Burning debuff, and provides 2 defense.
item.confluence.obsidian_skull.info: The Obsidian Skull is an immunity accessory that grants immunity to the Burning debuff normally inflicted by contact with Meteorite, Hellstone, and Hellstone Bricks.
item.confluence.obsidian_skull.info2: It does not grant immunity to lava or other fire-based attacks. It additionally provides 1 defense.
item.confluence.obsidian_skull.info3: Meteorite and Hellstone can be mined without Obsidian protection, as the player only takes damage when touching them in their placed block form; they can be mined from a distance without this immunity.
item.confluence.obsidian_skull.info4: However, this item makes the process much easier.
item.confluence.obsidian_skull_rose.info: The Obsidian Skull Rose is an accessory crafted from the Obsidian Skull and Obsidian Rose that combines their functionality, granting immunity to fire blocks and reduced damage from lava.
The Obsidian Skull Rose can be worn in a Social Accessory Slot as a vanity item.
item.confluence.obsidian_water_walking_b: Obsidian Water Walking Boots are an accessory which combines the abilities of the Water Walking Boots and the Obsidian Skull.
They allow the wearer to walk on water, honey, and shimmer, while also giving immunity to the Burning debuff.
They do not allow walking on lava.
item.confluence.paladins_shield.info: The Paladin's Shield is a Hardmode, post-Plantera shield accessory that functions primarily in multiplayer. While equipped, and when the wearer's health is above 25%, it grants all nearby players on their team the Paladin's Shield buff:
item.confluence.paladins_shield.info2: This buff causes 25% of any damage inflicted on them to transfer to the wearer of the shield instead. In both singleplayer and multiplayer, the Paladin's Shield also provides the wearer immunity to knockback (like the Cobalt Shield and its variants), and provides an additional 6 defense.
item.confluence.paladins_shield.info3: The Paladin's Shield has a 1/10 (10%) / 19/100 (19%) chance of being dropped by Paladins in the post-Plantera Dungeon.
item.confluence.paladins_shield.tooltip: Absorbs 25% of damage done to players on your team when above 25% life
item.confluence.panic_necklace.info: The Panic Necklace is an accessory, that, when equipped, grants the player the Panic! buff for 8 seconds when harmed by any source of damage besides fire blocks, increasing movement speed by 100%.
item.confluence.panic_necklace.info2: The Panic Necklace has a 1/5 (20%) chance of being obtained from destroying Crimson Hearts found in the Crimson or a 1/5 (20%) chance from Crimson Crates and Hematic Crates, which are fished in the Crimson.
item.confluence.panic_necklace.tooltip: Increases movement speed after taking damage
item.confluence.pda.info: The PDA is a post-Skeletron informational accessory which combines the functionalities of its ingredients, displaying fishing information, weather, moon phase, elevation, distance east/west, time, nearest valuable treasure, movement speed, current DPS, number of enemies killed, rare nearby creatures, and number of nearby enemies.
item.confluence.pda.info2: It has a very elaborate crafting tree (see Guide:Crafting a Cell Phone).
item.confluence.philosophers_stone.info: The Philosopher's Stone is a Hardmode accessory which decreases the Potion Sickness debuff duration by 25%.
item.confluence.philosophers_stone.info2: Therefore, 45 seconds after consuming a recovery potion while the Philosopher's Stone is equipped, another one can be consumed.
item.confluence.philosophers_stone.info3: It has a 1/6 (16.67%) / 1/7 (14.29%) chance to be dropped by Mimics.
item.confluence.philosophers_stone.toolt: Reduced the cooldown of Healing Potions
item.confluence.pink_horseshoe_balloon.i: The Pink Horseshoe Balloon is an accessory that grants immunity to fall damage, increases jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, grants a double jump, and grants +0.05 luck.

The height of the first jump is increased from 6 blocks to 10.5 blocks (~75% increase), while the double jump's height is increased from 7 blocks to 13 blocks, reaching a total of 23.5 blocks with both jumps.
Jump height is oddly reduced when underwater, reducing total underwater jump height from 17.5 blocks (8 blocks + 9½ blocks from Tsunami jump) to 15 blocks (7 blocks + 8 blocks from Tsunami jump).
item.confluence.platinum_watch.info: The Platinum Watch is a high-tier watch.
item.confluence.platinum_watch.info2: When equipped in an accessory slot or simply held in the inventory, a clock will appear in the upper-right corner of the playing screen, revealing the in-game time accurate to the last minute.
item.confluence.platinum_watch.info3: The Platinum Watch (or Gold Watch) is one of the three parts necessary to make the GPS, with the others being the Compass and the Depth Meter, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.platinum_watch.info4: The Platinum Watch can also be used to craft the 1 Second Timer.
item.confluence.pocket_mirror.info: The Pocket Mirror is a Hardmode immunity accessory that grants the player immunity to the Stoned debuff.
item.confluence.pocket_mirror.info2: It has a 1/40 (2.5%) / 1/20 (5%) chance of being dropped by Medusas.
item.confluence.pocket_mirror.info3: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Reflective Shades, which are a crafting material required to make the Ankh Charm, an accessory further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.power_glove.info: The Power Glove is a Hardmode accessory that doubles melee knockback and adds 12% increased melee speed.
item.confluence.power_glove.info2: It simply combines the effects of Feral Claws and Titan Glove with no benefits lost.
item.confluence.power_glove.info3: Additionally, the Power Glove enables autoswing on all melee weapons and whips and increases the size of all melee weapons by 10%.
item.confluence.putrid_scent.info: The Putrid Scent is a Hardmode accessory which increases damage and critical strike chance by 5% and decreases aggro by 400.
item.confluence.putrid_scent.info2: It has a 1/5 (20%) chance to be dropped by Corrupt Mimics.
item.confluence.putrid_scent.info3: It is unrelated to the Stinky debuff.
item.confluence.putrid_scent.tooltip: Enemies are less likely to target you
item.confluence.putrid_scent.tooltip2: 5% increased damage and critical strike chance
item.confluence.radar.info: The Radar is an informational accessory which displays the number of nearby enemies in a 125-tile radius around the player. The Radar has a 1/10 (10%) chance of being obtained from looting regular Chests found on or near the surface, or a 1/100 (1%) chance from Wooden and Pearlwood Crates obtained via fishing.
item.confluence.radar.info2: The Radar is one of the three parts necessary to make the R.E.K. 3000, with the others being the Tally Counter and the Lifeform Analyzer, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.ranger_emblem.info: The Ranger Emblem is a Hardmode accessory that increases ranged damage by 15%. It has a 1/4 (25%) chance to drop from the Wall of Flesh.
item.confluence.reflective_shades.info: The Reflective Shades are a Hardmode immunity accessory which combines the functions of the Blindfold and the Pocket Mirror, granting immunity to the Darkness and Stoned debuffs.
item.confluence.reflective_shades.info2: They are one of the ingredients required to make the Ankh Charm, which is further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.rek_3000.info: The R.E.K. 3000 is a post-Skeletron informational accessory which provides information about the number of nearby enemies, the player's enemy kill count, and nearby rare creatures.
item.confluence.rek_3000.info2: It combines the functionalities of its ingredients, the Radar, Tally Counter, and Lifeform Analyzer.
item.confluence.rocket_boots.info: Rocket Boots are an accessory that allows a player to fly for a period of around 1.6 seconds (100 game frames).
item.confluence.rocket_boots.info2: They require a jump from midair to activate (a double-jump, or a jump while falling).
item.confluence.rocket_boots.info3: During flight, they emit a jet animation that produces a good deal of light. Rocket Boots are purchased from the Goblin Tinkerer for 5 gold.
item.confluence.rocket_boots.info4: Flight time is reset immediately when the player lands on any solid object, or latches onto a surface with a Hook (even if the grapple is released early).
item.confluence.rocket_boots.info5: If the Cloud in a Bottle is also equipped, its double-jump effect will engage first; pressing and holding the jump key afterward while still in midair will then activate the Rocket Boots.
item.confluence.royal_gel.info: The Royal Gel is a pre-Hardmode accessory that pacifies most slimes when equipped, causing them to no longer pursue the player, and will deal no contact damage or fire projectiles, even if the player deals damage to them.
item.confluence.royal_gel.info2: The Royal Gel is always dropped from King Slime's Treasure Bag in Expert Mode.
item.confluence.royal_gel.info3: This does not apply to the following slimes:
item.confluence.royal_gel.info4: King Slime and his Spiked Slimes, though the normal Blue Slimes that King Slime spawns remain docile.
item.confluence.royal_gel.info5: Queen Slime and her Bouncy Slimes, Crystal Slimes, and Heavenly Slimes.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info: Sailfish Boots are an accessory that allows the user to sprint. This item is obtained from Wooden Crates and Iron Crates.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info2: When equipped, they allow the player to gain a speed boost after running for a certain distance continuously.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info3: By running in one direction, the player's movement speed increases up to 40%.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info4: The Sailfish Boots, Hermes Boots, and the Flurry Boots have identical functionality, with their only differences being aesthetic.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info5: In the case of the Sailfish Boots, the user will generate water particles coming out of their backs while running.
item.confluence.sailfish_boots.info6: All three listed boots are interchangeable when crafting Spectre Boots.
item.confluence.sandstorm_in_a_balloon.i: The Sandstorm in a Balloon is an accessory that combines the functions of the Sandstorm in a Bottle and the Shiny Red Balloon.

It boosts jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing the player's first jump's height to 10.5 tiles, and provides a double jump that can reach a height of 26.5 tiles, for a total height of 37 tiles.

Unlike most other double-jump balloons, the Sandstorm Balloon jump will put the player at risk of taking fall damage if they do not cancel it mid-jump or have fall damage immunity (e.g. a Lucky Horseshoe).

Oddly, the total jump height of the Sandstorm in a Balloon is reduced when underwater compared to the Sandstorm in a Bottle, reducing the player's total underwater jump height from 27 tiles to 22 tiles.
item.confluence.sandstorm_in_a_bottle.in: The Sandstorm in a Bottle is an accessory found inside Gold Chests within Pyramids.
it can also be obtained by throwing a Pharaoh's Mask into Shimmer, opening Oasis/Mirage Crates, and via crafting in Hardmode.

It is similar to the Cloud in a Bottle, providing a double-jump that allows for some extra height, but instead of a cloud beneath the feet, a sand jet appears and the character visually spins as they ascend on that jet.
The Sandstorm jump goes 15 tiles into the air, totalling 21 tiles when put together with the first jump. This is nearly twice as high as the height achievable with the Cloud in a Bottle.
item.confluence.sandstorm_on_a_bottle.to: Allows the holder to do an improved double jump
item.confluence.sextant.info: The Sextant is an informational accessory that displays the current moon phase.
item.confluence.sextant.info2: The Sextant can be received as a 1/34 (2.94%)[1] chance reward for completing a fishing quest for the Angler NPC, depending on the number of completed quests and other factors.
item.confluence.sextant.info3: The Sextant is one of the three parts necessary to make the Fish Finder, with the others being the Weather Radio and the Fisherman's Pocket Guide, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.shackle.info: The Shackle is an accessory that grants 1 point of defense. It is dropped by most kinds of Zombies with a 1/50 (2%) chance.
item.confluence.shackle.info2: Shackles may be useful early in the game when only few accessories are available.
item.confluence.shackle.info3: Typically, they should be replaced with more valuable accessories once out of free slots.
item.confluence.shark_tooth_necklace.inf: The Shark Tooth Necklace is an accessory which has a 1/149 (0.67%) / 1/75 (1.33%) chance to drop from Blood Zombies and Dripplers found during a Blood Moon.
It increases the player's armor penetration by 5 when equipped.
item.confluence.sharkron_balloon.info: The Sharkron Balloon is an accessory that combines the effects of the Tsunami in a Bottle and the Balloon Pufferfish.
item.confluence.sharkron_balloon.info2: It boosts jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30% increasing your first jump's height to ~10½ blocks (~75% increase), and provides a double jump that now goes 13 blocks, for a total height of 23½ blocks.
item.confluence.sharkron_balloon.info3: Jump height is oddly reduced when underwater, reducing your total underwater height from 17½ blocks (8 blocks + 9½ blocks from Tsunami jump) to 15 blocks (7 blocks + 8 blocks from Tsunami jump).
item.confluence.sharkron_balloon.info4: It can be combined with a Lucky Horseshoe at a Tinkerer's Workshop to make a Pink Horseshoe Balloon.
item.confluence.shield_of_cthulhu.info: The Shield of Cthulhu is a pre-Hardmode shield accessory that allows the player to perform a dash attack by double-tapping either the Left or Right key.
item.confluence.shield_of_cthulhu.info2: Dashing into an enemy deals 30 damage, recoils the player backward, and grants 0.07 seconds of invincibility frames.
item.confluence.shield_of_cthulhu.info3: The Shield of Cthulhu is always dropped from the Eye of Cthulhu's Treasure Bag in Expert Mode.
item.confluence.shield_of_cthulhu.toolti: Allows the player to dash into the enemy, sprinting to dsh
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info: The Shiny Red Balloon is an accessory that increases the player's jump height by 33% and jump speed by 30%, increasing the height that the player can jump from 6 blocks (12 feet) to ~10½ blocks (21 feet), effectively a ~75% boost.
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info10: With the Rocket/Spectre Boots, flight is accelerated, making the same flight time carry the player higher and/or farther.
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info11: The Frog Leg jump bonus stacks additively with the Shiny Red Balloon bonus, letting the first jump reach 16½ blocks (33 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info12: With wings, flight time is increased.
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info2: However, it oddly reduces jump height when underwater, from 8 blocks (16 feet) to ~7 blocks (14 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info3: The Shiny Red Balloon has a 1/4 (25%) of being found inside Skyware Chests on Floating Islands, as well as a 1/4 (25%) chance of being obtained from Sky Crates and Azure Crates.
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info4: The Shiny Red Balloon stacks with other jump-boosting accessories:
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info5: The Cloud in a Bottle's double-jump height is increased from 5 blocks (10 feet) to 9 blocks (18 feet), for a total jump height of 19½ blocks (39 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info6: The Blizzard in a Bottle's double-jump height is increased from 8 blocks (16 feet) to 14½ blocks (29 feet), for a total jump height of 25 blocks (50 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info7: The Sandstorm in a Bottle's double-jump height is increased from 14½ blocks (29 feet) to 26½ blocks (53 feet), for a total jump height of 37 blocks (74 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info8: The Fart in a Jar's double-jump height is increased from 10½ blocks (21 feet) to 18½ blocks (37 feet), for a total jump height of 29 blocks (58 feet).
item.confluence.shiny_red_balloon.info9: The Tsunami in a Bottle's double-jump height is increased from 7 blocks (14 feet) to 12 blocks (24 feet), for a total jump height of 23½ blocks (47 feet).
item.confluence.shoe_spikes.tooltip: Improved ability if combined with Climbing Claws
item.confluence.silver_watch.info: The Silver Watch is a mid-tier watch.
item.confluence.silver_watch.info2: The Tungsten Watch is an alternative to it. When equipped in an accessory slot or simply held in the inventory, a clock will appear in the upper-right corner of the playing screen, revealing the in-game time accurate to the last half an hour.
item.confluence.silver_watch.info3: Half an hour of Terraria game time is equivalent to half a minute of real-world time.
item.confluence.silver_watch.info4: The Silver Watch can be used to craft the 3 Second Timer.
item.confluence.sniper_scope.tooltip: 10% increased ranged damage and critical strike chance
item.confluence.sorcerer_emblem.info: The Sorcerer Emblem is a Hardmode accessory that increases magic damage by 15%. It has a 1/4 (25%) chance to drop from the Wall of Flesh.
item.confluence.spectre_boots.info: Spectre Boots are an accessory crafted from Rocket Boots and either Flurry Boots, Hermes Boots, Dunerider Boots, or Sailfish Boots, and combine their functionality.
item.confluence.spectre_boots.info2: During flight, they emit a white/blue cloud trail, but unlike the Rocket Boots, they do not produce any light. Their flight time is about 1.6 seconds, identical to Rocket Boots.
item.confluence.spectre_boots.info3: The effects of Spectre and Rocket Boots do not stack, though they do stack with Wings to increase flight time.
item.confluence.spectre_goggles.info: The Spectre Goggles are a Hardmode, post-Plantera accessory which allows the player to see Echo Blocks, Echo Platforms, Echo Walls, Ghostly Stinkbug Blockers, and tiles painted with Echo Coating while equipped.
item.confluence.spectre_goggles.tooltip: Enables Echo Sight, showing hidden blocks
item.confluence.star_cloak.info: The Star Cloak is a Hardmode accessory that causes three stars to fall around the player whenever the player takes damage. It consumes no mana.
item.confluence.star_cloak.info2: The stars pass through blocks until reaching the player's altitude, at which point they continue falling until hitting blocks.
item.confluence.star_cloak.info3: They pierce through an unlimited number of enemies.
item.confluence.star_cloak.info4: The Star Cloak has a 1/6 (16.67%) chance to be dropped by Mimics.
item.confluence.star_cloak.info5: The stars deal 75 / 150 / 225 damage which is not classified as any of the four damage types and therefore cannot be modified by any buffs or equipment. Furthermore, the stars have 25 armor penetration.
item.confluence.star_cloak.tooltip: Causes stars to fall after taking damage
item.confluence.star_veil.info: The Star Veil is a Hardmode accessory that combines the functions of the Star Cloak and the Cross Necklace, spawning falling star projectiles and increasing the TOTAL_LENGTH of the invincibility frames granted when the player is hurt.
item.confluence.step_stool.info: You can use Step Stool to upgrade its Extra Step from Smithing
item.confluence.step_stool.tooltip: Press ↑ key to stand higher, and press Shift key to down
item.confluence.stinger_necklace.info: The Stinger Necklace is a pre-Hardmode accessory that is obtainable after defeating the Queen Bee.
item.confluence.stinger_necklace.info2: This item combines the Shark Tooth Necklace and the Honey Comb accessories, giving the player 5 armor penetration as well as releasing 1–3 / 1–4 bees when the wearer takes damage and granting the Honey buff for 5 seconds.
item.confluence.stopwatch.info: The Stopwatch is an informational accessory that displays the player's current movement speed in miles per hour, e.g. "34 mph".
item.confluence.stopwatch.info2: The Stopwatch is one of the three parts necessary to make the Goblin Tech, with the others being the Metal Detector and the DPS Meter, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.sun_stone.info: The Sun Stone is a Hardmode, post-Golem accessory which has a 1/7 (14.29%) chance of being dropped by Golem.
item.confluence.sun_stone.info2: It grants the same stat bonuses as the Moon Stone;
item.confluence.sun_stone.info3: however, these bonuses only activate during the day.
item.confluence.sweetheart_necklace.info: The Sweetheart Necklace is an accessory which releases a concentrated burst of bees and grants the player the Panic! and  Honey buffs when damaged, increasing movement speed by 100% for 8 seconds and  health regeneration for 5 seconds.
item.confluence.sweetheart_necklace.tool: When damaged, the bee is released and the user is immersed in honey and increases movement speed
item.confluence.tackle_box.info: The Tackle Box is an accessory that decreases the chance of bait consumption while fishing.
item.confluence.tally_counter.info: The Tally Counter is a post-Skeletron informational accessory which displays how many enemies of a type have been killed.
item.confluence.tally_counter.info2: The Tally Counter will first display "Kill count unavailable" underneath the map/health area and, after an enemy has been attacked, the text will display how many times that enemy has ever been killed by all players combined in that world.
item.confluence.tally_counter.info3: The kill count will only display the last enemy struck by the player or their minions.
item.confluence.tally_counter.info4: It will count deaths from world creation rather than from when it was equipped.
item.confluence.tally_counter.info5: The Tally Counter is one of the three parts necessary to make the R.E.K. 3000, with the others being the Lifeform Analyzer and the Radar, and as such is a required ingredient in crafting the Shellphone.
item.confluence.terraspark_boots.info: The Terraspark Boots are a pre-Hardmode accessory crafted by combining Frostspark Boots and Lava Waders at a Tinkerer's Workshop, providing the benefits of both items.
item.confluence.terraspark_boots.info2: They are the final upgrade of the Hermes/Sailfish/Flurry/Dunerider and Water Walking Boots.
item.confluence.terraspark_boots.tooltip: Grants immunity to fire blocks and 7 seconds of immunity to lava
item.confluence.the_plan.info: The Plan is a Hardmode immunity accessory which combines the functions of the Fast Clock and the Trifold Map, granting immunity to the Slow and Confusion debuffs.
item.confluence.the_plan.info2: It is one of the ingredients required to make the Ankh Charm, which is further required to make the Ankh Shield.
item.confluence.tin_watch.info: The Tin Watch is a low-tier watch.
item.confluence.tin_watch.info2: When equipped in an accessory slot or simply held in the inventory, a clock will appear in the upper-right corner of the playing screen, revealing the in-game time accurate to the last hour. An hour of Terraria game time is equivalent to one minute of real-world time.
item.confluence.tin_watch.info3: The Tin Watch can be used to craft the 5 Second Timer.
item.confluence.titan_glove.info: The Titan Glove is a Hardmode accessory that doubles player-inflicted melee knockback.
item.confluence.titan_glove.info2: The Titan Glove has a 1/6 (16.67%) chance of being dropped by Mimics.
item.confluence.titan_glove.info3: It increases the size of melee weapons by 10%.
